# REASONING PROTOCOL - STATE TRACKING

## Step 0: LOAD
Read memory → Scan all layers → Map dependencies

## Step 1: TRACE FULL STATE FLOW
For every feature, track COMPLETE state chain:

UI State → User Action → API Request → Backend Logic → DB Operation → Response → UI Update

Example (Change Password with otp ):
- UI: User sees "Change Password" screen
- UI: Inputs old + new password → Validation state
- Action: Click "Save" → Loading state
- API: Request fired → Pending state
- Backend: Verify old → Hash new → Update DB
- DB: Transaction commit → Success/Failure
- Response: 200 OK or Error code + Message
- UI: Success → "Password updated" + Redirect
- UI: Error → Show message + Keep form

## Step 2: ANALYZE & EVALUATE
Current flow → Missing states? → Broken chain? → Max 3 iterations for BEST

## Step 3: PLAN
Fix ALL states in chain → Minimal touch → Single approach

## Step 4: EXECUTE (Auto)
Implement → Test EVERY state transition → No regression → Complete

## Step 5: E2E VALIDATE
Simulate user journey → Verify EACH visual state matches backend state

## Step 6: SYNC
Smart memory update → Git commit + push

## State Tracking Rules
- EVERY user action has visual state
- EVERY API call has loading/error/success state
- EVERY backend operation has matching UI feedback
- State transitions are instant and clear
- No silent failures
- No state mismatch between layers

## Core Rules
- One memory file
- Best &gt; First (3 tries)
- Complete fix
- DRY: Single source
- All layers sync
- Git sync
- git add -A && git commit -m "chore: sync local updates" && git push && docker compose up -d --build
